12.61	Three_Act_Tragedy	Three Act Tragedy	Three Act Tragedy is a work of detective fiction by Agatha Christie first published in the United States by Dodd, Mead and Company in 1934 under the title Murder in Three Acts and in the UK by the Collins Crime Club in January 1935 under Christie's original title. The US edition retailed at $2.00 and the UK edition at seven shillings and sixpence (7/6).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/21/Three_Act_Tragedy_US_First_Edition_Jacket_1934.jpg
